It provides Cinxi Enterprise, a security information and event management solution designed to meet enterprise-class log management, compliance, and security threat analysis requirements; Cinxi Midway, a 2U rack-mountable appliance designed for data collection, correlation, and storage requirements; Cinxi Ranger, a 1U rack-mountable appliance that offers security information and event management; and Cinxi Vault, an optional add-on storage component to accommodate long-term data retention. The company offers solutions for banking and financial, healthcare, government, and higher education industries. High Tower Software, Inc. was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Aliso Viejo, California. As of February 17, 2009, High Tower Software, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of netForensics, Inc. On February 25, 2009, High Tower Software, Inc. filed a voluntary petition for liquidation under Chapter 7 in the US Bankruptcy Court for the Central District Of California, Santa Ana.
